{"parentUuid":"e264cd1d-235a-4206-88b3-4156d9d0dc2a","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CLWBJZXc5ctKhe5FVtwCGF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Mutex** — mutual exclusion lock. Binary (locked/unlocked). Only the thread that acquired it can release it. Used to protect a shared resource so exactly one thread accesses it at a time.\n\n**Semaphore** — a counter. Initialized to N. `wait()` decrements (blocks at 0), `signal()` increments. Any thread can signal. Used to limit concurrency to N (e.g., connection pool of 5).\n\nKey differences:\n\n| | Mutex | Semaphore |\n|---|---|---|\n| Values | 0 or 1 | 0 to N |\n| Ownership | Yes — only owner unlocks | No — any thread can signal |\n| Purpose | Exclusive access | Rate-limit concurrency |\n| Analogy | Bathroom key (one holder) | Parking lot (N spots) |\n\nA binary semaphore (N=1) looks similar to a mutex but lacks ownership — any thread can release it, which makes it unsuitable for protecting critical sections where you need strict lock/unlock pairing."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30351,"cache_read_input_tokens":15866,"output_tokens":268,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30351,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZPUMpdGzMme7UoE9wdC1","type":"assistant","uuid":"c6134340-65e1-49a7-90b0-d6563691d1c7","timestamp":"2026-03-25T08:20:39.220Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/el-paso-v1","sessionId":"9ce0669c-7837-4474-b25e-69a8357ed8f4","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"marcus-sa/sandbox-agent-eval"}
